<body>
  <div class="accordion">
    <div class="image-box">
    <img src="images/visa.jpeg" alt="Accordion Image">
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-text">
      <div class="title">Visa</div>
    <ul class="faq-text">
      <li>
        <div class="question-arrow">
        <span class="question">How to Apply for a Visa?</span>
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down arrow"></i>
        </div>
        <p>* You can apply for a visa both online and offline. In case of offline visa applications, usually you need to download the application form and fill it with the required details. Then, you have to submit the filled application form supported by all required credentials at your concerned visa application center.</p>
        <p>* Different countries may have different application procedures for applying for visas. Many countries may not accept offline visa applications. Also, the cost involved in applying for a visa also differs from country to country.</p>
        <span class="line"></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="question-arrow">
          <span class="question">How to Check My Visa Status Online?</span>
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down arrow"></i>
        </div>
        <p>* Visa status check can be done online. In order to check your visa status online, you need to visit the visa status enquiry section of a particular consulate and keep certain information handy with you. To know you passport visa status, you may be required to put the following information:</p>
        <p>* Application ID</p>
        <p>* Passport number</p>
        <p>* You can also track your visa status by visiting a third party website and entering your passport number and date of birth. It is very easy to track your visa status by using your passport number.</p>
        <p></p>
        <span class="line"></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="question-arrow">
          <span class="question">What is difference between passport and visa?</span>
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down arrow"></i>
        </div>
        <p>* A passport stands as a proof that you are a legal citizen of a particular country. It is a document that is used for personal identification during travel to abroad.</p>
        <p>* It certifies your identity and nationality. On the other hand a visa is a kind of official document that gives you official permission to enter and stay at a particular country on temporary or permanent basis.</p>
        <span class="line"></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="question-arrow">
          <span class="question">Types of Visa Provisions?</span>
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down arrow"></i>
        </div>
        <p>1] Tourist Visa- 5 years,Multiple Entry,Applicants need to provide proof regarding their financial standing, that is, return ticket and sufficient money to spend during their stay in the country.This visa is not extendable.</p>
		<p>2] Transit Visa- 15 days,Single Entry/Double Entry,Confirmed ticket for onward journey.This Visa is not extendable.</p>
		<p>3] Business Visa- Maximum of 5 years,Multiple Entry,Documents that are proof of bonafide purpose such as a letter from the company and so on, along with proof of their financial standing.This Visa can be extended.</p>
		<p>4] Student Visa- 5 years or the period of the course, whichever is less,3 entries per the academy year.Admission proof in an Indian Institution along with letter of support from the guardian or parent. In addition to the above, applicants will also have to furnish a guarantee certificate from the bank regarding their financial standing.This Visa can be extended.</p>
		<p>5] Employment Visa- 1 year/ period of contract,Multiple Entry.Documents that prove employment, such as document of appointment.This Visa can be extended.</p>
		<p>6] 'X' entry Visa for foreigners who are of Indian origin- 5 years,Multiple Entry.Proof that the applicant is of Indian origin.This Visa can be extended.</p>
        <span class="line"></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="question-arrow">
          <span class="question">List of Required Identification Papers For Indian Nationals for visa?</span>
          <i class="bx bxs-chevron-down arrow"></i>
        </div>
        <p>* A National Passport that is valid.</p>
<p>* Photo ID card that has been provided by the Indian government or State government or Union Territory Administration to their employees/Voter ID card provided by the Election Commission of India.</p>
<p>* Emergency Certificate that has been provided by the Indian Embassy in Kathmandu.</p>
<p>* Identity Certificate that has been provided by the Indian Embassy in Kathmandu.</p>
<p>* Individuals above the age of 65 or below the age of 15 will not have to provide approved documents of identity but will have to furnish a document with their photograph confirming their identity and age such as Driving License, CGHS Card, PAN Card and Ration Card and so on.</p>
<p>* Children who are between the ages of 15 to 18 may be allowed to travel between Nepal/Bhutan and India based on the identity Certificate provided by their School Principal.</p>
        <span class="line"></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </div>
  </div>


  <script>
    let li = document.querySelectorAll(".faq-text li");
    for (var i = 0; i < li.length; i++) {
      li[i].addEventListener("click", (e)=>{
        let clickedLi;
        if(e.target.classList.contains("question-arrow")){
          clickedLi = e.target.parentElement;
        }else{
          clickedLi = e.target.parentElement.parentElement;
        }
       clickedLi.classList.toggle("showAnswer");
      });
    }
  </script>

